IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE PRESERVATION AND MAINTENANCE OF OPEN LANDS, TO PROMOTE A CONNECTION BETWEEN THE COMMUNITY AND THE LAND WITHIN AND TO PROVIDE NATURALIST-LED ENVIRONMENTAL EDUCATION TO SCHOOL CHILDREN AND SPECIAL WORKSHOPS TO CHILDREN, ADULTS AND FAMILIES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: SINCE ITS ESTABLISHMENT IN 1967, THE ASSOCIATION HAS ACQUIRED, PRESERVED AND MAINTAINED OVER 800 ACRES OF LOCAL NATIVE LANDSCAPES INCLUDING PRAIRIES, SAVANNAS, RAVINES, WOODLANDS AND WETLANDS FOR THE BENEFIT AND ENJOYMENT OF THE ENTIRE COMMUNITY. WE CONTINUE OUR EFFORTS TO RESTORE THE LAND TO ITS HISTORICAL LANDSCAPE AND MAINTAIN THESE CRITICAL HABITATS. IN ADDITION, TO PROMOTE A CONNECTION BETWEEN THE COMMUNITY AND THE LAND WITHIN IT, OUR PRESERVES ARE HOME TO OVER 12 MILES OF WALKING TRAILS WHICH ARE OPEN TO THE PUBLIC YEAR ROUND.THE ASSOCIATION ALSO PROVIDES NATURALIST-LED ENVIRONMENTAL EDUCATION TO SCHOOL CHILDREN AND SPECIAL WORKSHOPS OFFERED TO CHILDREN, ADULTS AND FAMILIES. OUR ENVIRONMENTAL EDUCATION PROGRAMS ARE DESIGNED TO DEVELOP AN UNDERSTANDING OF AND A LOVE AND RESPECT FOR THE NATURAL WORLD AROUND US BY INCLUDING HANDS-ON, PARTICIPATORY ACTIVITIES IN A NATURAL SETTING. ASSOCIATION ALSO COOPERATES WITH SEVERAL INSTITUTIONS PROMOTE THE SCIENTIFIC STUDY OF OUR PRESERVES.
IRS990.Desc: PRESERVATION AND MAINTENANCE OF OPEN LANDS FOR SCIENTIFIC AND EDUCATIONAL PURPOSES - PUBLIC HAS ACCESS TO THE LAND

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CONSERVATION EASEMENT WAS MODIFIED TO ADD FURTHER RESTRICTIONS WHICH PROTECT THE CONSERVATION VALUES OF THE EASEMENT.

THE ASSOCIATION RECOGNIZES REVENUE AND RECORDS AN ASSET BASED ON THE APPROXIMATE MARKET VALUE OF THE EASEMENT AT THE TIME OF CONTRIBUTION. AS OF MARCH 31, 2023, THE ASSOCIATION HAD TITLE OR CONSERVATION EASEMENTS TO LAND IN LAKE FOREST, ILLINOIS AMOUNTING TO $37,706,454 OF WHICH $21,243,768 WAS ACQUIRED THROUGH PURCHASE, $10,199,091 WAS RECEIVED BY CONTRIBUTIONS AND $6,263,595 WAS TRANSFERRED FROM A RELATED PARTY. THE $10,199,091 OF DONATED PROPERTY NOTED ABOVE HAS BEEN STATED AT AMOUNTS WHICH APPROXIMATE THE MARKET VALUE OF SUCH PROPERTY AT THE DATES THE INDIVIDUAL PARCELS WERE CONTRIBUTED TO THE ASSOCIATION. 1) THE ASSOCIATION HELD THIRTY EASEMENTS CONSISTING OF APPROXIMATELY 290 ACRES AT THE END OF THE YEAR. THIS WAS THE SAME AMOUNT OF EASEMENT'S AS THE PRIOR YEAR. ALL EASEMENTS ARE LOCATED IN THE STATE OF ILLINOIS AND PRIMARILY IN THE CITY OF LAKE FOREST. 2) NO EASEMENTS WERE SOLD, TRANSFERRED, RELEASED OR TERMINATED DURING THE YEAR COVERED BY THIS FORM 990 SCHEDULE D. 3)A. THE ASSOCIATION DOES NOT HOLD ANY EASEMENTS THAT ENCUMBER A GOLF COURSE OR PORTIONS OF A GOLF COURSE. B. THE ASSOCIATION DOES NOT HOLD ANY EASEMENTS THAT ARE WITHIN OR ADJACENT TO RESIDENTIAL DEVELOPMENTS AND HOUSING SUBDIVISIONS, INCLUDING EASEMENTS RELATED TO THE DEVELOPMENT OF PROPERTY. C. THE ASSOCIATION DOES NOT HOLD ANY EASEMENTS THAT WERE ACQUIRED IN A TRANSACTION DESCRIBED UNDER PURCHASE OF REAL PROPERTY FROM CHARITABLE ORGANIZATIONS IN NOTICE 2004-41. 4) THE ASSOCIATION MONITORED ALL THE ACREAGE OF ITS EASEMENTS DURING THE YEAR COVERED BY THIS FORM 990 SCHEDULE D THROUGH PHYSICAL INSPECTION AND OTHER MEANS. 5) THE TOTAL STAFF HOURS INCURRED FOR MONITORING AND ENFORCING NEW OR EXISTING EASEMENTS DURING THE YEAR COVERED BY THIS FORM 990 SCHEDULE D WERE 124 HOURS. THE LIST OF EXPENSES INCURRED ARE AS FOLLOWS: EASEMENT MONITORING $4,613 G&A COSTS $71,354 6) THE ASSOCIATION HAS ONE EASEMENT ON A LOG CABIN THAT WAS RECEIVED IN 1998. THEREFORE THE ASSOCIATION HAS NOT ACQUIRED AN EASEMENT ON BUILDINGS OR STRUCTURES AFTER AUGUST 17, 2006.

THE ARTISTIC COLLECTIONS CONSIST OF PAINTINGS, A SCULPTURE AND A STONE RING. ALL ARTISTIC COLLECTIONS WERE DONATED. THE ARTIST COLLECTIONS ARE ON DISPLAY IN THE OFFICES AND ON THE GROUNDS TO PROVIDE INSPIRATION AND FURTHER OUR EXEMPT PURPOSE.
THE ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE TO BE USED TO FURTHER THE MISSION OF THE ORGANIZATION.

THE ASSOCIATION IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT ENTITY AS DESCRIBED IN SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES ON RELATED INCOME. IT IS ALSO EXEMPT FROM STATE INCOME TAXES FOR RELATED INCOME AND QUALIFIES FOR CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTION DEDUCTIONS IN REGARD TO ITS DONORS. THE ASSOCIATION WOULD BE SUBJECT TO BOTH FEDERAL AND STATE TAXES ON UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME, THOUGH IT DID NOT HAVE ANY FOR THE YEARS ENDING MARCH 31, 2023 AND 2022. AS OF MARCH 31, 2023 AND 2022, THE ASSOCIATION DID NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT IT IS OBLIGATED TO DISCLOSE. ADDITIONALLY, THERE WERE NO RETURNS UNDER REVIEW OR OPEN TO REVIEW BY TAXING AUTHORITIES IN EXCESS OF STATUTORY PERIODS. THE ASSOCIATION FOLLOWS A CONSERVATIVE APPROACH OF RESEARCH AND OPEN DISCLOSURE IN REGARD TO ITS TAX-EXEMPT STATUS AND POSITIONS HELD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS HAS DELEGATED THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE REVIEW AND APPROVAL OF THE FORM 990 TO THE AUDIT COMMITTEE. THE AUDIT COMMITTEE DOES A COMPLETE REVIEW OF THE FORM 990 WITH THE CPA FIRM AND APPROVES THE FILING OF THE FORM 990. THE CHAIRMAN OF THE AUDIT COMMITTEE REPORTS THE COMMITTEES PROCEDURES AND APPROVAL PROCESS OF THE FORM 990 TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND OFFICERS ARE REQUIRED ON AN ANNUAL BASIS TO SUBMIT A STATEMENT OF THEIR STATUS REGARDING THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OBTAINS COMPARATIVE COMPENSATION REPORTS FOR EXECUTIVE DIRECTORS FROM THE FOREFRONT ORGANIZATION. THIS INFORMATION ALONG WITH THE ANALYSIS OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S PERFORMANCE ARE THE BASIS FOR DETERMINING THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S COMPENSATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COPIES OF THE ASSOCIATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST AT THE ASSOCIATION'S OFFICES FOR A NOMINAL FEE.
THE OVERSIGHT AND SELECTION PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PAGE 1, ITEM B - AMENDED RETURN
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ASSOCIATION IS AMENDING ITS FORM 990 TO REPORT A MODIFICATION TO A CONSERVATION EASEMENT HELD BY THE ASSOCIATION. THE AMENDMENT IS CHANGING THE ASSOCIATION'S RESPONSE TO THE QUESTION ON SCHEDULE D, PART II, LINE 3 - " NUMBER OF CONSERVATION EASEMENTS MODIFIED, TRANSFERRED, RELEASED, EXTINGUISHED, OR TERMINATED BY THE ORGANIZATION DURING THE TAX YEAR" FROM 0 TO 1. THE ASSOCIATION ALSO ADDED AN EXPLANATION FOR THE AMENDMENT ON SCHEDULE D, PART XIII SUPPLEMENTAL INFORMATION.
